      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "DRIVE SEARCH PANEL"
      },
      {
        "type": "blank"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "Drive Search presents the search function from a disk drive"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "viewpoint.  It displays a select list of drives attached to your"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "system which contains useful information about each drive."
      },
      {
        "type": "blank"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "Individual fields are explained below:"
      },
      {
        "type": "blank"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "FILE TYPES TO DISPLAY+- Specifies the types of files that are to be"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "displayed.  You can specify `D` for directories only, `F` for"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "files only, or `B` for both files and directories."
      },
      {
        "type": "blank"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "SEARCH SUBDIRECTORIES+- This field lets you specify whether the"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "search should be limited to the first level of the specified"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "path or to all levels (via recursive search)."
      },
      {
        "type": "blank"
      },
      {
        "type": "blank"
      },
